    <h2>Women's Ministry Programs</h2>
    <h3>Prayer Ministry</h3>
    <p>Rev. Jean Johnson is leader of the Prayer Ministry. The ministry has prayer request forms at the church door entrances and in the church office. Fill out the red prayer request form and give it to Rev. Johnson or leave it at the office.</p>
    <h3>Finance & Program Ministry</h3>
    <p>Ruth McConnell is leader of the Finance & Program Ministry. This ministry coordinates the financial aspects of the Shiloh Women's Ministry. They work hard to make sure the finances are in order and that the Women's Ministry programs are a success.</p>
    <h3>Mission Ministry</h3>
    <p>Shenee' Williams is leader of the Missions Ministry. The Missions Ministry will be working closely with Shiloh Baptist Church and community mission projects.</p>
    <h3>Hospitality Ministry</h3>
    <p>Queen Stewart-Williams is leader of the Hospitality Ministry. This ministry does a beautiful job coordinating the decorations and refreshments for the various Shiloh Women's Ministry church programs.</p>
    <h3>Women's Ministry Sunday School Class</h3>
    <p>Loretha Davis, Shiloh Women's Ministry Director, is teacher of the Women's Ministry Sunday School class. The current study, written by Judy Baker, is called "Embracing Grace (Reconciling Relationships with People and God)". Please join us for our Women of the Word Sunday Morning Bible Study at 9:45 AM in Room 314.</p>
